        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana: Ice Plant/Cold Store of minimum 20-ton capacity, introduced by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry &amp; Dairying, Government of India, aims to provide the subsidy for 20-ton capacity ice plant/cold storage units, supports the establishment of ice plants or cold storage facilities with a minimum capacity of 20 tons to improve fish preservation and cold chain infrastructure in Haryana.\nThis centrally sponsored scheme is jointly funded 50% by the Central Government and 50% by the State Government. Beneficiaries must submit an undertaking in their DPR agreeing to keep the unit operational, cover all post-construction costs, and supply ice to fishers and fish farmers at affordable prices.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- The project cost is ₹80,00,000/-\n\n> **Subsidy Distribution :**\n\n\n1. A 40% subsidy is available for the General Category.\n1. A 60% subsidy is offered for SC (Scheduled Caste) and Women beneficiaries.\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The subsidy for 20-ton capacity ice plant/cold storage units under Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana (PMMSY) supports the establishment of ice plants or cold storage facilities with a minimum capacity of 20 tons to improve fish preservation and cold chain infrastructure in Haryana.",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
